cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new approach to address the training difficulty in variational language models by using a Gaussian Copula Variational Autoencoder. The paper focuses on machine learning and neural networks, which are typically covered in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also discusses language models, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks for image processing, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the use of copulas to model correlation and dependencies, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
